Package: fireR
Title: Download and Load USGS Fire Data and EPA Ecoregion Boundaries
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person("Noah", "Weidig", email = "noah.weidig@ufl.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides fast, convenient access to USGS fire datasets and EPA/CEC
    ecoregion boundaries. For MTBS (Monitoring Trends in Burn Severity),
    downloads the composite burned-area extent shapefile and returns it as
    either an 'sf' or 'terra' SpatVector object with optional filtering by year
    and incident type. For the Southeast FireMap (SE FireMap) Annual Burn
    Severity Mosaics, downloads ZIP archives for one or more years (2000-2022)
    of predicted Composite Burn Index (CBI) values covering 78 ARD Landsat
    tiles across the southeastern United States. Also provides loaders for
    Commission for Environmental Cooperation (CEC) North America ecoregion
    boundaries at Levels 1-3, and US EPA ecoregion boundaries at Levels 3-4
    (with optional state boundaries).
